						<div class="postbody">As long as it works alright on a real system, it should be fine.  Sounds ok to me so far, except there's no way to escape from the idle routine.  I almost would've recommended a CPU-cycle based interrupt to call it, but I suppose that's getting kinda far from how the actual games work even if it is escapeable.  No big deal, the system can just get reset.
<br />
<br />What would it do on tracks that don't use the idle routine (like Skate or Die 2 except the title), just return from idle maybe?</div>

